It was an honour to engage with Indonesian President Prabowo Subianto during his state visit. His appreciation for PM @narendramodi ‘s vision of women-led development, India’s efforts to combat malnutrition through Poshan Abhiyan and the push for technical textiles by GOI was truly encouraging.

We also spoke about the growing India-Indonesia partnership—a collaboration rooted in shared cultural heritage and a commitment to economic growth. Grateful for his time & insights 🙏

latestPosts.caption: This is the CCD video .. the Chaos behind the Conundrum called Davos.. often I travel to cities where I have no time to breathe , let alone look at the sights and hear the distinct local sounds ; taste the food or embrace the local way of life . Tired with bruised feet and broken nails but a gladdened heart - I leave a town crossing my fingers that one day Il come back and see the people for what they are in their natural habitat and not when events become a habit in their day to day life.. this was me for 1 hour as I prepped to come back to my country.. Delhi ho ya Davos .. momo khana banta hai , lactose intolerant hue toh kya hua hot chocolate peena banta hai .. I was wrapped and packed in woollens galore as if all the cold in the world will be caught by me .. CCD - we survived & thrived .. till next time ❤️❤️#wef2025 🥳🥰

Had the privilege of an inspiring discussion with Børge Brende, President & CEO of the World Economic Forum, during #WEF25 in Davos.

I shared the progress of the Alliance for Global Good , with WEF as a key Network Partner, and highlighted two transformative partnerships that are paving the way for global gender equity:

1️⃣ Empowering Women Entrepreneurs: Partnering with 56 Commonwealth countries to support 100,000 women-owned businesses in India, with plans to expand globally. This initiative provides access to financial tools, expertise, and global markets to scale women-led enterprises.

2️⃣ Leadership in the Energy Sector: Collaborating with SAWIE under the US-India Strategic Partnership Forum to drive gender-responsive reforms and boost women’s representation in energy leadership. With women holding only 22% of leadership roles in this sector, this initiative is vital for fostering inclusive progress.

Børge’s enthusiasm and steadfast commitment to these initiatives reaffirm our shared mission to empower women as drivers of transformative global change.

📍 Davos @worldeconomicforum @borgebrende 

#WEF25 #Davos2025

The ‘Gate’way to inclusion and innovation—a meeting with Bill Gates at the World Economic Forum.

It has been an honor to collaborate with Bill and his team over the years on issues of equity and innovation. His unwavering commitment to these causes continues to inspire me.

What is truly humbling is witnessing how he balances his monumental success with genuine humility. Bill has an incredible way of making those around him feel valued, never overwhelming with his achievements but always eager to listen, learn, and inspire.

With his feet firmly on the ground, he continues to give wings to countless dreams @thisisbillgates

As I prepare to attend the World Economic Forum in Davos, I am energised by the opportunity to engage with global industry captains, policymakers, and thought leaders to champion a women-led agenda.

At the core of my mission is the drive to foster partnerships that advance women’s interests in capital, climate change, enterprise, and innovation. I will proudly represent The Alliance for Global Good: Gender Equity & Equality as its Founder & Chairperson; highlighting its collaboration with CII & the support we have collectively received from the Gates Foundation.

In the coming days, I aim to:
1️⃣ Amplify conversations about gender equity in economic and environmental policy.
2️⃣ Showcase how inclusive leadership can transform industries.
3️⃣ Build actionable partnerships to ensure women remain central to global progress.

Stay tuned as I share key insights and outcomes from Davos over the next three days. Let’s create a future that is inclusive, innovative, and impactful.

#Davos2025 #WEF2025

Most people pack for their kids , organise for their spouses , plan for the whole jing bang we call family .. and then there are our parents we need to take care of … but what if we only plan, pack , organise a small holiday around our parents ? 2024 was life changing in many ways , it was a year of reflection and new beginnings.. but one thing which will now become a yearly norm for me is to plan a trip just with me and my parents. It’s a task especially if they have been divorced.. they pick up on issues 40 years old . But it’s fun to see them the way they are .. unapologetic, innocent yet well travelled, well lived .. I travelled with my parents alone, they giggled , they gossiped , they were melancholic, they were melodious .. they were just Ma and Papa.. my plans for 2025 with them are ready .. what about you ?? #plan2025 ❤️❤️#parents ❤️

Why stop at 1 when you can help a 100,000 !!! An evening to collaborate with compassion, create opportunities for skilling  and providing sustainable livelihoods for 1 lac widows in India . It was a privilege to bring together CII and the Loomba Foundation in the presence of Cherie Blair to help provide the necessary skills sets & create financial opportunities for 1 lac widows to thrive , to live their lives with dignity and to lead us to an inclusive future .. #creatingpartnerships #changinglives 😊@cherieblairfndn @followcii @loombafoundation

Thrilled to welcome Cherie Blair KC tomorrow for the launch of the transformative #HerSkillHerFuture initiative.

Led by the Women’s Collective Forum in collaboration with The Loomba Foundation and CII, this initiative aims to empower 100,000 widows by equipping them with critical skills and opportunities to achieve financial independence and lead lives of dignity.

This program is a testament to the power of partnerships and the belief that when women are empowered, they empower the world. Together, we are taking a bold step towards a future where no woman is left behind.

Looking forward to seeing the incredible impact this initiative will have on countless lives 😊

DANGER #This post may carry with it the danger of inspiring you to give your Mom an extra hug today #Age is just a number, and my 74-year-old mom is proof that life is limitless when you live it on your own terms. She’s not just walking into her golden years—she’s lifting her way there, one gentle weight at a time. 

When we look at our aging parents, we often imagine them growing old from ‘our’ perspective. We set boundaries , conditions, modalities to their behaviour, their needs. We think they should slow down, follow ‘new rules,’ or adjust to life as we see fit. But old age isn’t about limits—it’s about living as they so desire— finally. It’s about strength, dignity, and a little encouragement from us to embrace the life they love.

My mom’s not just about morning walks; she’s about exploring her strength, testing her boundaries, and showing me every day that age isn’t a barrier—it’s a milestone to thrive beyond. Let’s care for our parents not by reshaping their world but by honoring it, supporting it, and celebrating every moment with them. ❤️💪

Here’s to living & loving their way❤️❤️
2024: A year of action, impact, and transformation! Grateful for every milestone and the incredible people who made it unforgettable 🥰🥰

This is for you—the average Joe or Jane—who reads in silence, supports in silence, and cheers in silence. I want you to know: I hear you, I see you, and I am deeply grateful for you. ❤️

Every time the world is unkind  for faltering, every time destiny seems to deny  what one deserves, every time one stands at a crossroads feeling like I just can’t go on—you are the strength that inspires me. You are the voice in my head that whispers, “Not now. Don’t give up now.”

As you read this, I want you to know that I pray for you. I pray that life brings you the same benevolence and kindness you’ve shown me. You are more than a supporter; you are a part of my journey, my courage, and my reason to keep going. ❤️❤️

Thank you for being you. Thank you for walking up to me at airports, on the street, or in a quiet corner of a restaurant, just to offer a kind word or a smile. Thank you for standing by me, often without even knowing it.

You are extraordinary, and you matter more than you know ❤️ Anime credit @min7j_un
